-- Rostelecom to Get $420 Million for Election Cameras, IFX Says
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-03-11T15:14:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/rostelecom-to-get-420-million-for-election-cameras-ifx-says.html
OAO Rostelecom, a Russian telephone
and Internet operator, will receive 12.4 billion rubles ($420
million), for setting up and maintaining web cameras to monitor
the March 4 presidential elections, Interfax said today, citing
a company statement.  The company signed contracts with the Communications
Ministry to set up cameras that broadcast voting at around
91,000 polling stations live on the Internet and to maintain the
recordings until the end of the year, Interfax said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Torrey Clark at 
